{
  "id": "L3",
  "title": "Al supermercato",
  "content": [
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In this lesson, you will learn how to ask for items at a supermarket, 'un supermercato'. Let's start by getting an employee's attention."
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E01",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Mi scusi",
        "meaning": "Excuse me"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L3_P01",
      "data": {
        "word": "Scusi",
        "phonetic": "[sk'u-zi]",
        "tip": "The 'sc' is pronounced like the 'sk' in 'school'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E02",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Dov'è...?",
        "meaning": "Where is...?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L3_P02",
      "data": {
        "word": "Dov'è",
        "phonetic": "[doh-VEH]",
        "tip": "The accent on 'è' means the stress falls on that final syllable."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V01",
      "data": {
        "Il latte": "The milk"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V02",
      "data": {
        "Il pane": "The bread"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "In Italian, most nouns are preceded by an article like 'il', which means 'the'. You'll almost always see 'il pane', not just 'pane'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V03",
      "data": {
        "In fondo": "At the end"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V04",
      "data": {
        "A destra": "On the right"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V05",
      "data": {
        "Qui": "Here"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E03",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Altro?",
        "meaning": "Anything else?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L3_S01",
      "title": "Asking for Help",
      "setting": "You are in a supermarket and can't find anything. You see an employee and approach them for help.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Get the employee's attention",
          "chatbot_message": null
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask where the milk is",
          "chatbot_message": "Sì?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask where the bread is",
          "chatbot_message": "Il latte è in fondo a destra."
        },
        {
          "title": "Answer the employee",
          "chatbot_message": "Il pane è qui. Altro?"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Great! Now let's ask for something by weight. 'Vorrei' is the most polite way to say 'I would like...'"
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E04",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Vorrei...",
        "meaning": "I would like..."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L3_P03",
      "data": {
        "word": "Vorrei",
        "phonetic": "[vor-r'ei]",
        "tip": "Try to roll the 'rr' sound. It takes practice!"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V06",
      "data": {
        "Un etto": "100 grams"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V07",
      "data": {
        "Due": "Two"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "It's very common in Italy to ask for things in 'etti'. So, to ask for 200 grams, you say 'due etti'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V08",
      "data": {
        "L'uva": "The grapes"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V09",
      "data": {
        "Il formaggio": "The cheese"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L3_P04",
      "data": {
        "word": "Formaggio",
        "phonetic": "[for-m'ad-djo]",
        "tip": "The 'ggio' sound is like the 'j' in 'judge'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E05",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "È in offerta?",
        "meaning": "Is it on sale?"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V10",
      "data": {
        "Certo": "Certainly"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E06",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Grazie",
        "meaning": "Thank you"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E07",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Prego",
        "meaning": "You're welcome"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L3_S02",
      "title": "Asking for Quantities",
      "setting": "The conversation continues. The employee has just asked if you need anything else. You are at the fruit and cheese counter.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Ask for 200 grams of grapes",
          "chatbot_message": "Il pane è qui. Altro?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask if the cheese is on sale",
          "chatbot_message": "Certo. Due etti di uva. Altro?"
        },
        {
          "title": "Thank the employee",
          "chatbot_message": "Sì, è in offerta."
        },
        {
          "title": "Acknowledge their response",
          "chatbot_message": "Prego!"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "tip",
      "text": "Fantastic job! You have all your items. Now it's time to pay at the checkout, 'la cassa'."
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V11",
      "data": {
        "La cassa": "The checkout"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E08",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Buongiorno",
        "meaning": "Good day"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "pronunciation",
      "item_id": "L3_P05",
      "data": {
        "word": "Buongiorno",
        "phonetic": "[bwon-j'or-no]",
        "tip": "Use this to greet people in shops during the day. It's more common than 'ciao'."
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V12",
      "data": {
        "Un sacchetto": "A bag"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E09",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Per favore",
        "meaning": "Please"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E10",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Sono... euro",
        "meaning": "It is... euros"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "vocabulary",
      "item_id": "L3_V13",
      "data": {
        "Dieci": "Ten"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E11",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Ecco",
        "meaning": "Here you are"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "expression",
      "item_id": "L3_E12",
      "data": {
        "phrase": "Arrivederci",
        "meaning": "Goodbye"
      }
    },
    {
      "type": "interactive_scenario",
      "scenario_id": "L3_S03",
      "title": "At the Checkout",
      "setting": "You've finished shopping and are now at the checkout counter with a new person, the cashier.",
      "conversation_flow": [
        {
          "title": "Greet the cashier",
          "chatbot_message": "Buongiorno."
        },
        {
          "title": "Ask for a bag",
          "chatbot_message": null
        },
        {
          "title": "Respond and pay",
          "chatbot_message": "Certo. Sono dieci euro, per favore."
        },
        {
          "title": "Say goodbye",
          "chatbot_message": "Grazie. Arrivederci!"
        }
      ]
    }
  ]
}